                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #146r #146v #147r" facs="001 002 149 150 150">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso), 146r, 146v, 147r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#ii(recto)" facs="002">Fol. ii(recto)</locus>
                    <desc>
                    title page. Holy Scripture, written in Ge‘ez and Amharic, Third part
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Translated by Ethiopian church scholars from Ge‘ez into Amharic
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003">Fol. iiir(ecto)</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Table of Contents for Three Volumes; the Table of Contents for volume four, the New Testament, is on <locus target="#iiiv(erso)" facs="004">fol. iiiv(erso)</locus>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#iiiv(erso)" facs="004">Fol. iiiv(erso)</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      in blue ink, top of page: "This book belongs to Agafari Täkläyäs Wolde Mika‘el, given to him from Emperor Ḫaylä Śǝllase to be a memorial for the era of exile, in 1929 (EC =1936/7) when we are in a foreign land."
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዛንቱ፡ መጽሏፍ፡ ዖአጋፋሪ፡ ተክሇየስ፡ ወሌዯ፡ ሚካኤሌ፡ ዖተውሕበ፡ ልቱ፡ እምቀዲማዊ፡ ኃይሇ፡ ሥሊሴ፡ ንጉሠ፡ ነገሥት፡ ከመ፡ ይኩን፡ ሇዛክረ፡ ነገር፡ በመዋዔሇ፡ ስዯት፡ አመ፡ ፩፱፻፳፱፡ ዒመት፡ እንዖ፡ ሀልነ፡ ውስተ፡ ብሔረ፡ ባእዴ፡</foreign>
                      In blue ink at bottom of page: ―Ato Ḫǝruy Ṭǝbäbu bought this book with his money on 19 Mäskäräm 1969 (EC).‖
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#145v" facs="149">Fol. 145v</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    in blue ink, "[This is the] ninth [copy of the published book]; Agafari Täkläyäs was given this book." "This book belongs to Ato Ḫǝruy Ṭǝbäbu who bought it with his money from a woman named Wayzero Azänäč Aba Šawǝl, wife of Agafari Täkläyäs in 1969 (EC)."
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
